### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client)
### Click "Send Request" above each ### block

@host = http://localhost:4000
@email = demo@gym.com
@password = demo123

### 1. Health check
GET {{host}}/api/health

### 2. Register a new user
POST {{host}}/api/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "secret123",
  "name": "New User"
}

### 3. Login (copy the token from the response below)
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 4. Get current user
GET {{host}}/api/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get your gym state
GET {{host}}/api/state
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Update your gym state (example: add a goal)
PUT {{host}}/api/state
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "data": {
    "exercises": [],
    "schedule": [],
    "logs": [],
    "metrics": [],
    "goals": [
      { "id": "abc123", "title": "Test goal from REST", "target": "100kg", "done": false }
    ]
  }
}

### 7. Delete account (careful!)
# DELETE {{host}}/api/account
# Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
